SIMPLE: thus
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thus
<hw>Thus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>thus</ets>,
better <ets>tus</ets>, frankincense. See <er>Thurible</er>.]</ety>
<def>The commoner kind of frankincense, or that obtained from the Norway
spruce, the long-leaved pine, and other conifers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thus</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thus
<hw>Thus</hw> <pr>(⟦th⟧us)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>thus</ets>, AS. <ets>⟦edh⟧us</ets>; akin to OFries. & OS.
<ets>thus</ets>, D. <ets>dus</ets>, and E. <ets>that</ets>; cf. OHG.
<ets>sus</ets>. See <er>That</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In this or
that manner; on this wise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Thus</qex> did Noah; according to all that God commanded him,
so did he.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. vi. 22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Thus</qex> God the heaven created, <qex>thus</qex> the
earth.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To this degree or extent; so far; so; <as>as,
<ex>thus</ex> wise; <ex>thus</ex> peaceble; <ex>thus</ex>
bold</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Thus</qex> far extend, <qex>thus</qex> far thy bounds.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thussock</ent>⟦br⟧
